<%# requirement.md revisit: "download will open modal and show the progress bar and once 100%
    done then modal will close automatically and xlsx will download." Shared Bootstrap modal —
    same "one instance per console, driven entirely by data-* on whatever link triggers it" shape
    shared/_confirm_dialog.html.erb already established — for any download that streams real
    bytes through this app rather than a plain, instant static link (Admin::ExportFilesController
    #download, Admin::ImportFilesController#sample). Driven by download_progress_controller.js.
    data-bs-backdrop="static"/data-bs-keyboard="false" — this one closes itself once the download
    actually finishes, not on a stray click/Escape while it's still in flight.

    Usage — on any download link:
      data-action="click->download-progress#start"
      data-download-progress-filename-param="participants.xlsx" (optional fallback filename, used
        only if the response's own Content-Disposition header doesn't carry one) %>
<div class="modal fade" id="downloadProgressModal" tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="true"
     data-bs-backdrop="static" data-bs-keyboard="false" data-download-progress-target="modal">
  <div class="modal-dialog modal-sm modal-dialog-centered">
    <div class="modal-content border-0 shadow">
      <div class="modal-body text-center py-4">
        <p class="text-muted font-size-14 mb-3" data-download-progress-target="label">Preparing your download&hellip;</p>
        <div class="progress" style="height: 6px;">
          <div class="progress-bar" role="progressbar" style="width: 0%" data-download-progress-target="bar"></div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-muted font-size-12 mt-2 mb-0" data-download-progress-target="percent">0%</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
